<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="30" type="further specimens studied">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="30">Further specimens studied.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="30">ECUADOR:</emphasis>
&quot;Pichincha-Quito, 23.vi.1985, Gustavo 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Morejón[p]”">Morejon[p]&quot;</normalizedToken>
(1 male, 1 female, MNCN); &quot;Pichincha, Alluriquin, 6.v.1948, F. Grazo leg.[h]&quot; (1 male, NMPC).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="30">No difference between both sexes were observed and also no variability in the colouration apparent.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="30">
Aedeagus (Figs 76, 77 in 
<bibRefCitation author="Cobos, A" journalOrPublisher="Archivos de Instituto de Aclimatacion (Almeria)" pageId="27" pageNumber="44" pagination="103 - 165" refId="B19" refString="Cobos, A, 1956. Ensayo monografico sobre las Anthaxia Eschs. (Coleoptera, Buprestidae) de America. Primera parte: Subgeneros Cylindrophora Sol. y Paracuris Obenb. Archivos de Instituto de Aclimatacion (Almeria) 5: 103 - 165" title="Ensayo monografico sobre las Anthaxia Eschs. (Coleoptera, Buprestidae) de America. Primera parte: Subgeneros Cylindrophora Sol. y Paracuris Obenb." volume="5" year="1956">Cobos 1956</bibRefCitation>
) very short, widely spindle-shaped, median lobe simply pointed apically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="30">Length: 4.0-5.5 mm; width: 1.7-2.0 mm.</paragraph>
